text: The Tabernacle Baptist Church, at 1431 Broad St. in Selma, Alabama, was built in 1922. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2013. It is a Baptist church in the National Baptist Convention, USA, and was designed by African American architect David T. West.
